-------------------------
Ever Success "Hedaka" 286
-------------------------

NOTE: Often, this board will have a single 64K EPROM (27512)
      which simulates a 16-bit wide pair of 32K EPROMs (27256s).

      To correctly burn the single 27512, first split the 64K
      binary BIOS to Even and Odd halves.  (This is the same step
      you would follow to burn two 27256s).  Then

        (1) burn the Even 32K half to the low half of the 27512
            (ie, at offset 0000, fills 0000-7FFF)

        (2) burn the Odd 32K half to the high half of the 27512
            (ie, at offset 8000, fills 8000-FFFF)


Filename   Port      Description
--------   -------   ---------------------------------------------------------
V036B200   HDK_200   286 EverTech
V036B210   HDK_210   286 EverTech, with built-in EMS

